>On a 76 is the pin on which the gas pedal pivots supposed come out?  My pedal
>has one of the hinge points gaped to the point it can be removed with the pin
>in place, but I suspect this is not right and why my pedal feels floppy.  I
>know that on my 181 the two holes are the same size and the pin is just pushed
>out the side to free the gas pedal.  However, on my 76 bus the pin is so
>rusted I can't tell if is is fixed or not.  I gave it a few good whacks with
>the punch and hammer but it didn't budge.  I don't want to beat too hard until
>I know it's supposed to move.

Use some penetrating oil and knock it out. The pin should go all the way through.

